President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring November 12-18, 2017, as American Education Week. In the proclamation, Trump emphasizes the importance of a quality education in achieving the American Dream and highlights the role of parents, teachers, and advocates in shaping children's education. He also emphasizes the need to protect and preserve state and local control over schools and to provide a wide range of high-quality educational choices for parents. Trump directs the Department of Education to prioritize increasing high-quality education programs in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) and to make it easier for companies to provide apprenticeship programs. He also stresses the importance of family involvement in education and its positive impact on student achievement. Trump calls on states and communities to support high-quality education to meet the needs of all students.